  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe\u0026#39;ve all been there: you click the Chrome icon, and then... You wait. That seemingly endless pause before your homepage finally loads can be frustrating. Tired of the delay? So was I, so I optimized Chrome for a faster startup.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"enable-webpage-preloading\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e6 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Enable Webpage Preloading\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1196\" height=\"716\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Performance tab in Chrome showing preload pages option\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/performance-tab-in-chrome-showing-preload-pages-option.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e One of the first things I did to \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/speed-up-chrome-preload-webpages/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emake Google Chrome boot fast was to enable webpage preloading\u003c/a\u003e. This feature allows Chrome to anticipate which pages I might visit next, so it can start loading them in the background before I even click on a link.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThis way, when I start the browser, it doesn\u0026#39;t have to wait for me to click on links; they\u0026#39;re already partially loaded. To enable webpage preloading, head to \u003cstrong\u003eSettings \u0026gt; Performance \u0026gt; Speed\u003c/strong\u003e and enable the \u003cstrong\u003ePreload pages\u003c/strong\u003e toggle.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eChrome offers a couple of options in this menu: \u003cstrong\u003eExtended preloading\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003eStandard preloading\u003c/strong\u003e. I personally prefer \u003cstrong\u003eExtended preloading\u003c/strong\u003e because it allows Chrome to load most of the pages based on my browsing behavior.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"configure-startup-behavior-for-a-quick-launch\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e5 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Configure Startup Behavior for a Quick Launch\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1195\" height=\"683\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Google Chrome startup settings menu on PC\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-startup-settings-menu-on-pc.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Like most people, I have a particular set of webpages I open every time I launch Chrome. However, opening each webpage by entering the address, clicking the homepage shortcuts, or even navigating through the bookmarks menu can be time-consuming.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eInstead, I\u0026#39;ve configured Chrome to open these pages automatically on startup, and it\u0026#39;s made a huge difference. Now, when I launch Chrome, it not only loads my main page but also loads the other pages I regularly visit in the background. So by the time I switch to a second tab, it\u0026#39;s already ready.\u003c/p\u003e        \u003col\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Open Chrome, click the \u003cstrong\u003ethree-dot menu\u003c/strong\u003e icon in the top right corner, and select \u003cstrong\u003eSettings\u003c/strong\u003e.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        In the left-hand menu, select the \u003cstrong\u003eOn startup\u003c/strong\u003e tab.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Choose the \u003cstrong\u003eOpen a specific page or set of pages\u003c/strong\u003e option.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Click \u003cstrong\u003eAdd a new page\u003c/strong\u003e to enter the URLs of the pages you want Chrome to open automatically upon startup.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHaving each of my favorite pages open when I start working is a massive time saver.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"disable-energy-saver-for-maximum-performance\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e4 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Disable Energy Saver for Maximum Performance\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1197\" height=\"683\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Google Chrome showing energy saver option turned off\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-chrome-showing-energy-saver-option-turned-off.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/enable-google-chrome-energy-saver-mode/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eChrome\u0026#39;s built-in Energy Saver mode\u003c/a\u003e is great if you\u0026#39;re on the go and need to extend your laptop\u0026#39;s battery life. It achieves this by limiting background activities and slowing down CPU-intensive tasks.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eHowever, since I mostly work from home, conserving battery isn\u0026#39;t a priority for me. Disabling this feature has noticeably improved my Chrome experience, both in terms of boot time and overall performance.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eYou can go to \u003cstrong\u003eSettings \u0026gt; Performance \u0026gt; Power\u003c/strong\u003e and turn off the \u003cstrong\u003eEnergy Saver\u003c/strong\u003e toggle. If you prefer it to activate automatically when your battery reaches a lower level, you can leave the toggle on and choose \u003cstrong\u003eTurn on only when your battery is at 20% or lower\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"enable-gpu-rasterization\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Enable GPU Rasterization\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1198\" height=\"731\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Enable GPU Rasterization in Google Chrome\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/enable-gpu-rasterization-in-google-chrome.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Rasterization is the process in which Chrome converts vector-based images or objects into pixels that can be displayed on the screen. By default, Chrome relies on the CPU to handle this task. However, with GPU rasterization enabled, Chrome offloads this process to the graphics card, which is better equipped for such tasks.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThis results in a faster rendering experience, which is particularly noticeable when you launch Chrome. The GPU rasterization option isn\u0026#39;t available in Chrome\u0026#39;s regular settings menu, but you can easily enable it through Chrome\u0026#39;s hidden flags menu.\u003c/p\u003e        \u003col\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Type \u003cstrong\u003echrome://flags/\u003c/strong\u003e in the URL bar and hit \u003cstrong\u003eEnter\u003c/strong\u003e.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        In the search box that appears, type \u003cstrong\u003eGPU rasterization\u003c/strong\u003e.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        From the drop-down menu next to the option, select \u003cstrong\u003eEnabled\u003c/strong\u003e.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Finally, click the \u003cstrong\u003eRelaunch\u003c/strong\u003e button for the changes to take effect.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eUnfortunately, Chrome\u0026#39;s Flags aren\u0026#39;t permanent settings. Sometimes, Flags are removed without warning, while at other times, they\u0026#39;re integrated into Chrome\u0026#39;s actual settings. So, you\u0026#39;ll have to keep an eye on this one.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"limit-the-number-of-extensions\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Limit the Number of Extensions\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1197\" height=\"722\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Extensions menu in Google Chrome\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/extensions-menu-in-google-chrome.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Each time I start Chrome, all my extensions must load and initialize, which takes time and resources. So, while extensions are incredibly useful, having too many significantly slows down Google Chrome\u0026#39;s performance.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eTo avoid this, I\u0026#39;ve reduced the number of extensions I use in Chrome. I\u0026#39;ve carefully selected only the ones that I truly need and use daily. This simple change has boosted Chrome\u0026#39;s startup speed, as fewer extensions mean fewer processes running in the background when it boots up.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"turn-off-automatic-proxy-detection\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e1 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Turn Off Automatic Proxy Detection\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1051\" height=\"601\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Windows 11 Settings app showing automatic proxy settings toggle turned off\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows-11-settings-app-showing-automatic-proxy-settings-toggle-turned-off.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e I recently started using AdGuard DNS to block ads, trackers, and malicious domains. However, soon after setting it up, I noticed a significant delay before the first page loaded each time I launched Chrome.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAfter a bit of digging and some trial and error, I found the culprit through a \u003ca href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/Adguard/comments/1c9v0kc/slow_initial_loading_times_with_chrome/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eReddit thread\u003c/a\u003e. It turned out that Automatic Proxy Detection was the main cause of the delay, and disabling it fixed the problem for me instantly. You can do the same by heading to \u003cstrong\u003eSettings \u0026gt; Network \u0026amp; Internet \u0026gt; Proxy\u003c/strong\u003e and disabling the \u003cstrong\u003eAutomatically detect settings\u003c/strong\u003e toggle.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
